## Auth (Privy Setup)
- Wrap app in `<PrivyProvider>` in layout.tsx
- Show "Sign In" button in navbar if not authenticated
- Supported login methods: Google, Apple
- On auth: store user's wallet address in Supabase `users` table (upsert)
- Solana embedded wallet via Privy — enable in Privy dashboard settings

---

## Data Layer (Codex.io)

Key endpoints to use:
- Trending tokens: `GET /tokens/trending?networkId=1399811149` (Solana network ID)
- Token metadata: `GET /tokens/{address}`
- Token price: `GET /tokens/{address}/price`
- OHLCV for chart: `GET /tokens/{address}/ohlcv`
- Recent trades: `GET /tokens/{address}/swaps`
- Holders: `GET /tokens/{address}/holders`

All Codex.io requests should go through a Next.js API route (`/api/codex/...`) to keep the API key server-side.

---

## Jupiter Integration (Swaps)

Use Jupiter v6 API — no API key needed:
- Quote: `GET https://quote-api.jup.ag/v6/quote?inputMint=...&outputMint=...&amount=...`
- Swap: `POST https://quote-api.jup.ag/v6/swap` — returns a transaction to sign
- Sign with Privy's Solana embedded wallet (`useSolanaWallets()`)
- Broadcast via Alchemy RPC

